        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(cron): skip deleteAfterRun and preserve counters for manual runs (#83538)",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n`openclaw cron run` (manual/debug runs) on a `deleteAfterRun` at-job deletes the job on success — consuming the one-shot and preventing its scheduled execution. Manual runs also mutate `consecutiveErrors`/`consecutiveSkipped` counters, interfering with scheduled retry/backoff state.\n\nThis PR adds an `isManual` flag to `applyJobResult` so manual runs preserve the job and leave scheduled execution state untouched.\n\n## Root cause\n\n`applyJobResult()` has no concept of manual vs scheduled runs. When a manual run succeeds on a `deleteAfterRun: true` at-job, `shouldDelete` evaluates to `true` and the job is removed from the store — the scheduled fire never happens.\n\nAdditionally, manual error/skipped/success outcomes unconditionally mutate `consecutiveErrors` and `consecutiveSkipped` counters, which control retry backoff and auto-disable behavior for scheduled runs.\n\n## Changes\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `timer.ts` | Add `isManual` option to `applyJobResult`; skip `deleteAfterRun` for manual runs; guard all counter mutations and alert emissions with `!isManual` |\n| `ops.ts` | Pass `isManual: true` from manual run completion and invalid-persisted-run handling |\n| `timer.regression.test.ts` | 5 new tests: manual ok/error preserve job, manual doesn't increment/reset counters |\n\n## Tests\n\n```\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/cron/service/timer.regression.test.ts\n ✓ cron (45 tests) 144ms\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  45 passed (45)\n```\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior or issue addressed**: Manual `cron run` on a `deleteAfterRun` at-job deletes it, preventing scheduled execution. Manual runs also mutate scheduled retry counters.\n- **Real environment tested**: Local OpenClaw checkout at `aa92a4a5b0`, macOS arm64, Node.js v24.10.0.\n\n### Source-level proof\n\n```\nMain branch applyJobResult():\n  - shouldDelete = kind === \"at\" && deleteAfterRun && status === \"ok\"\n    → no manual discriminator, always deletes on success\n  - consecutiveErrors incremented unconditionally on error\n  - consecutiveSkipped incremented unconditionally on skip\n\nFix branch:\n  - shouldDelete = wouldDelete && !opts?.isManual\n    → manual runs never trigger deletion\n  - Counter mutations guarded: if (!opts?.isManual) { ... }\n    → manual runs don't affect retry/backoff state\n```\n\n### Regression test coverage\n\n```\n✅ manual ok on deleteAfterRun at-job → job preserved, not deleted\n✅ manual error on deleteAfterRun at-job → job preserved, not deleted  \n✅ scheduled ok on deleteAfterRun at-job → job deleted (unchanged behavior)\n✅ manual error does not increment consecutiveErrors (pre-existing=3 → still 3)\n✅ manual success does not reset consecutiveErrors (pre-existing=3 → still 3)\n```\n\n- **What was not tested**: Live `openclaw cron run` CLI flow (requires a running gateway with a configured `deleteAfterRun` at-job). The `isManual` flag propagation from `ops.ts` to `applyJobResult` is validated at the unit level.\n\nCloses #83538\n",
        "branch": "fix/cron-delete-after-run-manual-83538",
